FT  01 MAR 93 / Construction Contracts: Research facility in Hampshire
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MATTHEW HALL has won a Pounds 12.7m building engineering services contract
for the new centre for deep sea oceanography in Southampton.
Working for main contractor, Wimpey Construction UK, Matthew Hall has been
called in to supply and install the mechanical, electrical, public health
and fire engineering services.
The 25,000 sq metre building is being jointly funded by the Natural
Environment Research Council and the University of Southampton and will
house laboratories, offices, workshops, lecture theatres and other service
facilities.
