<TEXT>
THE BANK of England faced fresh criticism of its handling of the failed Bank
of Credit and Commerce International yesterday when 43 MPs, including Labour
frontbenchers, called for a review of Mr Eddie George's appointment as
governor-designate.
The MPs called in a Commons early day motion for Mr George's appointment to
be reviewed by the cross-party Treasury and Civil Service select committee,
which this week published a report highly critical of the Bank's performance
in the BCCI affair.
