<HEADLINE>
FT  27 FEB 93 / London Stock Exchange: Income funds look to Gas
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN, JOEL KIBAZO and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STRONG support for British Gas, apparently from income funds seeking to take
advantage of the 3.5 per cent yield on the final dividend, drove the shares
up sharply to close 9 higher at 298p. Buying was additionally fuelled by
reports that James Capel, the leading agency broker, had upgraded its
dividend forecasts for the company after Gas's 1992 figures announced on
Thursday.
The income funds are expected to be keen supporters of the stock until it
goes ex-dividend on May 10. However, some specialists cautioned that the
outcome of the inquiry being carried out by the Monopolies and Mergers
Commission may be made public before that time.
</TEXT>
