<TEXT>
Sir, Your editorial, 'Paying for roads' (February 23), prompts me to inform
you of the real cost of road privatisation. My company's vehicles use the
Severn River toll crossing every day. It now costs Pounds 9.30 for each
heavy goods vehicle to cross into Wales. In the nine months since
privatisation these tolls have been raised twice and are now 55 per cent
higher than at this time last year.
